      "text": "I'll help you investigate this **WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR** BSOD. Let me gather diagnostic information from your system using PowerShell and Python tools.",
      "timestamp": 1783146221031
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is experiencing a Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) with the stop code: **WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR**. They want me to investigate this using proper enterprise root cause analysis and tell them:\n\n1. The fixability score (using iFix methodology)\n2. How reliable the fix would be\n3. Whether they can spend time improving PC temperature4. Component assessment without stress testing\n5. Use PowerShell and Python tools\n\nFirst, I need to understand the current environment - this is a Windows system (win32 platform). I should:\n1. Check system information2. Look for crash dumps\n3. Check Windows Event Logs for related errors\n4. Check system temperatures and hardware status\n\nLet me start by gathering information about the system and looking for relevant logs.",
      "timestamp": 1783146263764
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-WinEvent -LogName System -MaxEvents 100 | Where-Object { $_.Id -eq 41 -or $_.Id -eq 1001 -or $_.ProviderName -eq 'Microsoft-Windows-WHEA-Logger' } | Select-Object TimeCreated, Id, LevelDisplayName, Message | Format-Table -AutoSize\", \"description\": \"Check system event log for WHEA errors\"}",
      "output": "(no output)",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783146266707
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
